##* {{RQ:Bacon Essayes|chapter=Of Usurie. XLI.|page=240|passage=The ''Diſcommodities'' of ''Vſury'' are: Firſt, that it makes fevver Merchants. For vvere it not, for this Lazie Trade of ''Vſury'', Money vvould not lie ſtill, but vvould, in great Part, be Imployed vpon '''Merchandizing'''; VVhich is the ''Vena Porta'' of VVealth in a State.}}
